data.enText: very great; felt or experienced very strongly
profound changes in the earth's climate

data.chText: 父亲的去世深深地影响了我们全家。
data.enText: My father's death had a profound effect on us all.

data.chText: 知识渊博的；理解深刻的；深邃的

data.enText: needing a lot of study or thought
profound questions about life and death

simple_means.memory_skill: pro 前面 + found 基础 → 有基础在前面 → 深远的

ex.chText: 房子后面曾经有个很深的池塘。
ex.enText: There was a deep pond behind the house.

ex.chText: 那两位哲学家的谈话对我而言太深奥了。
ex.enText: The conversations between the two philosophers were too deep for me.

ex.chText: 那位政治家在访问地震灾区时表示了深切的慰问。
ex.enText: The politician expressed his deep sympathy when he visited the quake-hit area.

synonyms.bx: 形容具体事物时，指由表及里或由上到下的深度；形容抽象事物时，指内容深奥的或感情深切的。

ex.chText: 两名男演员在万丈悬崖上打斗的场面给我留下了深刻印象。
ex.enText: The scene in which two actors fought on an abysmal cliff gave me a deep impression.

synonyms.bx: 通常指由上到下的深度不可测的。

ex.chText: 他的舞蹈触及了人类内心深处的某种东西。
ex.enText: His dance touches upon something profound in the human mind.

ex.chText: 这位导演的童年经历深深地影响了他的电影。
ex.enText: The director's childhood experience has a profound impact on his film.

ex.chText: 他们怀着浓厚的兴趣做此项研究。
ex.enText: They did the research with profound/deep interest.

synonyms.bx: 多用于形容抽象事物，如影响或效果；指感情深切时可与 deep 换用。

tr: situated at or extending to great depth
too deep to have been sounded or plumbed
example: the profound depths of the sea
the dark unfathomed caves of ocean"-Thomas Gra

tr: showing intellectual penetration or emotional depth
far-reaching and thoroughgoing in effect especially on the nature of something
example: the fundamental revolution in human values that has occurred
committed the fundamental error of confusing spending with extravagance

value.def: You use profound to emphasize that something is very great or intense.

example.ex: ...discoveries which had a profound effect on many areas of medicine.
example.tran: 对很多医学领域产生了深刻影响的发现

example.ex: The overwhelming feeling is just deep, profound shock and anger...
example.tran: 最强烈的感觉就是深深的震惊和愤怒。

example.ex: This has profoundly affected my life...
example.tran: 这给我的生活带来了深刻的影响。

example.ex: In politics, as in other areas, he is profoundly conservative.
example.tran: 就像在其他领域一样，他在政治方面也非常保守。

value.def: A profound idea, work, or person shows great intellectual depth and understanding.

example.ex: This is a book full of profound, original and challenging insights.
example.tran: 这本书充满了深刻、新颖、令人深思的见解。

example.ex: ...one of the country's most profound minds.
example.tran: 该国知识最渊博的人之一

value.tran: 深刻的；深奥的；知识渊博的

partsOfSpeech.dec: found 基础 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 基础；地基
found 基础 + er 表名词 → 奠基者
funda〔= fund〕基础 + ment 表名词 → 基础
pro 前面 + found 基础 → 有基础在前面 → 深远的
pro 前面 + fund 基础 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 深刻；深度
un 无 + found 基础 + ed 表形容词 → 没有根基的 → 无事实根据的
